Structural basis of epigenetic protection of mouse lymphoid progenitor cells by Dnmt1

Norimasa Iwanami, Kohei Takeshita, Divine-Fondzenyuy Lawir, Isao Suetake, Shoji Tajima, Katarzyna Sikora, Ines Trancoso, Connor Oâ€™Meara, Iliana Siamishi, Thomas Clapes, Eirini Trompouki, Yousuke Takahama, Makoto Furutani-Seiki, Hisato Kondoh, Yasushige Yonezawa, Michael Schorpp and Thomas Boehm

Summary

This document provides the R code and accompanying explanations to reproduce Figures 1 B-C, 7 A-C, as well as Supplementary Figure 6 from the manuscript with working title â€œStructural basis of epigenetic protection of mouse lymphoid progenitor cells by Dnmt1â€ by Iwanami et al..
The analysis starts with partially processed methylation and gene expression analysis results and walks the reader through the data processing underlying the manuscript figures. A copy of this document will be deposited on GitHub under https://github.com/katsikora/Iwanami2019_SupplementaryCodeAndData_B upon publication. The code is formatted in a way to facilitate understanding and interpretation by a lay R user. This code is authored by Katarzyna Sikora.

  • Figure 1C: â€œhttps://owncloud.gwdg.de/index.php/s/uqSNUHxH1PIwJZn/downloadâ€ (medaka amplicon single CpG values extracted for the target intervals from Potok et al.Â 2013., RData format); â€œhttps://owncloud.gwdg.de/index.php/s/IBcLPYo46QiZGzm/downloadâ€ (Potok et al.Â 2013 intervals lifted over to MEDAKA1 genome and corrected for primer placement, bed format),
  • Figure 7A: â€œhttps://owncloud.gwdg.de/index.php/s/rablpH3ijlfw90d/downloadâ€ (mouse HSC CpG methylation values aggregated over DMRs, RData format),

Figure 1B. Interval mean methylation ratio in zebrafish data.

Significance testing for differential methylation in the zebrafish dataset:

## logit transform the interval means
plotdat$logit25 <- logit(p = plotdat$BetaMean, percents = FALSE, adjust = 0.025)

GSv <- unique(as.character(plotdat$GeneSymbol))
res <- data.frame(GSv, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
res$MT <- NA
res$WT <- NA
res$logitMT <- NA
res$logitWT <- NA
res$pval <- NA

for (i in seq_along(GSv)) {
    td <- plotdat[plotdat$GeneSymbol %in% GSv[i], ]
    
    res$MT[i] <- mean(td$BetaMean[td$Group %in% "dnmt1m/m"])
    res$WT[i] <- mean(td$BetaMean[td$Group %in% "dnmt1+/+"])
    res$logitMT[i] <- mean(td$logit25[td$Group %in% "dnmt1m/m"])
    res$logitWT[i] <- mean(td$logit25[td$Group %in% "dnmt1+/+"])
    
    z <- t.test(x = td$logit25[td$Group %in% "dnmt1m/m"], y = td$logit25[td$Group %in% 
        "dnmt1+/+"], var.equal = TRUE)
    res$pval[i] <- z$p.value
    
}

res <- res[order(res$pval), ]
res

Significance testing for differential methylation in the medaka dataset:

## logit transform the interval means
plotdat$logit25 <- logit(p = plotdat$BetaMean, percents = FALSE, adjust = 0.025)

GSv <- unique(as.character(plotdat$GeneSymbol))
res <- data.frame(GSv, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
res$MT <- NA
res$WT <- NA
res$logitMT <- NA
res$logitWT <- NA
res$pval <- NA

for (i in seq_along(GSv)) {
    td <- plotdat[plotdat$GeneSymbol %in% GSv[i], ]
    
    res$MT[i] <- mean(td$BetaMean[td$Group %in% "dnmt1m/m"])
    res$WT[i] <- mean(td$BetaMean[td$Group %in% "dnmt1+/+"])
    res$logitMT[i] <- mean(td$logit25[td$Group %in% "dnmt1m/m"])
    res$logitWT[i] <- mean(td$logit25[td$Group %in% "dnmt1+/+"])
    
    z <- t.test(x = td$logit25[td$Group %in% "dnmt1m/m"], y = td$logit25[td$Group %in% 
        "dnmt1+/+"], var.equal = TRUE)
    res$pval[i] <- z$p.value
    
}

res <- res[order(res$pval), ]
res
